<subSubSection id="6AB59980FFF3FF93FF67FE4FA8F239D1" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2210CA0BFFF3FF93FF67FE4FA8F239D1" blockId="5.[151,1437,505,748]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF3FF93FF67FE4FA876392E" bold="true" box="[151,274,505,531]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E5AFB188FFF3FF93FEEBFE4FA80B392E" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1903" box="[283,367,505,531]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Mesilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF3FF93FEEBFE4FA80B392E" box="[283,367,505,531]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Mesilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="E5AFB188FFF3FF93FD2BFE4FAA00392E" authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1893" box="[731,868,505,531]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Macrophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF3FF93FD2BFE4FAA00392E" box="[731,868,505,531]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Macrophyes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by having elongated and thin body; long and thin legs; median apophysis on anterior side of the tegulum and by having a large retrolateral, marginal tooth on distal side of chelicerae, but can been distinguished by the long and laminar median apophysis; ventral tegular projection absent and long embolus basally inserted on the tegulum (
<figureCitation id="BA94D68EFFF3FF93FC60FDD3AAB03942" box="[912,980,613,639]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-68@6.[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A-H. Mesilla vittiventris Simon, 1903. Male (ICN-Ar 9696):A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, retrolateral view; E palp, ventral view; F leg I, ventral view. Female (ICN-Ar 6271): B habitus, dorsal view; G epigynum, ventral view; H epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations:A, atrium; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum. Scale bars: A, B, F: 2mm; C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–H: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506506/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Figs 3</figureCitation>
C−E). Females are characterized by their short copulatory ducts, restricted to the posterior portion of the epigynum and with small, tubular seminal receptacles on medial region; long, wide, divergent lateral borders, with rounded apex (
<bibRefCitation id="463EB7FAFFF3FF93FBD1FD1BAD9C39FA" author="Brescovit, A. D." box="[1057,1272,685,711]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" pagination="101 - 106" refId="ref5208" refString="Brescovit, A. D. (1992) Revisao das aranhas do genero Macrophyes O. Pickard-Cambridge, da regiao Neotropical (Araneae, Anyphaenidae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 36, 101 - 106." type="journal article" year="1992">Brescovit 1992: 12</bibRefCitation>
, 13; 1997: figs 150−151; 
<figureCitation id="BA94D68EFFF3FF93FEFAFD67A8ED39D1" box="[266,393,721,748]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-68@6.[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A-H. Mesilla vittiventris Simon, 1903. Male (ICN-Ar 9696):A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, retrolateral view; E palp, ventral view; F leg I, ventral view. Female (ICN-Ar 6271): B habitus, dorsal view; G epigynum, ventral view; H epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations:A, atrium; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum. Scale bars: A, B, F: 2mm; C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–H: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506506/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Figs 3G, H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
